    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="504"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d504">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5731/120</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Assistant Secretary of State</hi> (<hi
                        rend="italic">Sayre</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-29">May 29,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Norwegian Minister called to say that he had been instructed by his
                    Government to propose the entering into negotiations for a trade agreement with
                    this Government, but that his Government hoped very much that the whale oil
                    question could be cleared up before negotiations were entered into because of
                    the feeling of irritation in Norway over the action by the United States in
                    imposing an excise tax on whale oil last year. He said that he was expecting to
                    see the Secretary on Friday to deliver this message to him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">rancis</hi>] B. S[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ayre</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
